{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/use-r-to-calculate-boilerplate-for-accounting-analysis-f4a5b64e9b0d", "time": 1683007723.182251, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/use-r-to-calculate-boilerplate-for-accounting-analysis-f4a5b64e9b0d/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Use R to Calculate Boilerplate for Accounting Analysis | by Jinhang Jiang | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Use R to Calculate Boilerplate for Accounting Analysis", "description": "In textual analysis, Boilerplate is a combination of words that can be removed from a sentence without significantly changing the original meaning, such as \u201cmore than million in\u201d or \u201cat the end of.\u201d\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0165410115000658", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.ifrs.org/news-and-events/2013/06/iasb-chairs-speech-breaking-the-boilerplate/", "anchor_text": "Hoogervorst, 2013", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://github.com/jinhangjiang/Boilerplate", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 15}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jinhangjiang/", "anchor_text": "LinkedIn", "paragraph_index": 17}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jinhangjiang/", "anchor_text": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jinhangjiang/", "paragraph_index": 19}], "all_paragraphs": ["In textual analysis, Boilerplate is a combination of words that can be removed from a sentence without significantly changing the original meaning, such as \u201cmore than million in\u201d or \u201cat the end of.\u201d According to Mark Lang and Lorien Stice-Lawrence, Boilerplate has become a particular problematic attribute in annual reports, identified by regulators and standard setters, and their analysis showed that annual report disclosure (from over 15,000 companies) improved as Boilerplate was reduced. The details of the study can be found here.", "One of the reasons why Boilerplate affects the quality of annual disclosure is Boilerplate may provide opportunities to hide information, reducing overall informativeness (Hoogervorst, 2013).", "I am using 30 corporation social responsibility reports as data to demonstrate how to calculate the Boilerplate. They are all from companies in the communication industries, such as AT&T, Sprint Corporation, and the like. They are all written in English and pdf format.", "In my demonstration of calculation, I will comply with Mark Lang\u2019s definition of Boilerplate: the percent of words in reports from sentences that contain at least one of the \u201cboilerplate\u201d phrases (4-word phrases, or tetragrams).", "In this step, we used the \u201ctm\u201d package and the \u201ctokenizers\u201d package. To generate proper tetragrams and reduce the amount of computation, we removed numbers in this step. Since all the original documents are pdfs, the \u201ctokenize_sentences\u201d function can recognize the irregular paragraph line breaks adequately and split the text into sentences.", "In this step, I generated tetragrams and had all the tetragrams in one list for further analysis since Mark Lang\u2019s measure requires looking for the common 4-word phrases in all documents level.", "In this step, I manually set the thresholds that only the tetragrams that occur in between 30% and 75% of the entire corpus of documents will be used for calculation. The reason why I have to set a ceiling is explained in Mark Lang\u2019s paper. But generally speaking, the tetragrams sometimes contains innocuous phrases or regulatory disclosure, which will convey informative content. The purpose of Boilerplate is to discover how uninformative the document is, so I have to exclude the most popular tetragrams from the calculation.", "The partial output looks like the following:", "When I initially started this assignment, I ran into many troubles in this step since the final output will be creasy if I messed this part up. One sentence may have no tetragrams at all or has multiple tetragrams at the same time. It is very easy to double or triple count the number of words in one sentence. To solve the problem, I set a temporary variable to flag sentences to avoid multiple counting.", "Let\u2019s recap the definition of Boilerplate:", "After I flagged all the boilerplate sentences, I generated the length of each document:", "The code for the final calculation:", "The final output looks like the following:", "Calculating Boilerplate helps to get a better understanding of the informativeness of a set of reports in accounting textual analysis. When doing the calculation, you have to be cautious about double-counting boilerplate sentences.", "I have intended to avoid using \u201clapply\u201d and used many \u201cfor loops\u201d in my code. It can effectively help structure and organize the codes for debugging purposes. Also, multiple tasks require assigning outputs to environment variables multiple times. Since R has consistently increased the performance of \u201cfor loops,\u201d the speed of \u201cfor loops\u201d is not as bad as it used to be.", "For your reference, you can find all the R codes here.", "A python version can be found here:", "Please feel free to connect with me on LinkedIn.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Data Scientist at Walmart Inc. | https://www.linkedin.com/in/jinhangjiang/"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Ff4a5b64e9b0d&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fuse-r-to-calculate-boilerplate-for-accounting-analysis-f4a5b64e9b0d&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/sig